did.physloc: Please note: This collection is located in off-site storage and may require 2-3 days notice for retrieval. Contact Special Collections for more information.
did.abstract: This collection consists of the records of the Sahel Regional Financial Management Project that was organized to improve the financial management of Sahelian institutions that manage funds from the U.S. Agency for International Development. The collection includes correspondence, telefaxes, reports, evaluations, financial and legal records, and more. The countries involved were the United States, Senegal, Gambia, Chad, Burkina Fasa, Mali, and Niger.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: Permission to publish material from Records of the Division of Outreach and International Affairs, Sahel Regional Financial Management Project must be obtained from Special Collections, Virginia Tech.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Researchers wishing to cite this collection should include the following information: Records of the Division of Outreach and International Affairs, Sahel Regional Financial Management Project, RG 35/1/1c, Special Collections, Virginia Tech, Blacksburg, Va.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: The collection was transferred to Special Collections in May 1990.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The processing, arrangement, and description of the collection was completed in December 2019.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The Sahel Regional Financial Management Project was organized to improve the financial management of Sahelian institutions that manage funds from the U.S. Agency for International Development. The countries involved were the United States, Senegal, Gambia, Chad, Burkina Fasa, Mali, and Niger. The Sahel is the ecoclimatic and biogeographic zone of transition, in Africa, between the Sahara desert to the north and the Sudanian Savanna to the south.

The Sahel Regional Financial Management Project began in the Office of International Programs, established in 1975. It is the predecessor to the Division of Outreach and International Affairs, which was established in 2003.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of the records of the Sahel Regional Financial Management Project that was organized to improve the financial management of Sahelian institutions that manage funds from the U.S. Agency for International Development. The collection includes correspondence, telefaxes, reports, evaluations, financial and legal records, and more. It is divided by country and material types.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is in original order, primarily by country and material type.
